Name.BusinessNameLine1: Girl Scouts of Gulfcoast Florida Inc

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Girl Scouts is the premier leadership development program for girls. We are an advocate for all girls and an expert in their growth and development. Girl Scouts of Gulfcoast Florida, Inc. provides the Girl Scout Leadership Experience to girls in 10 counties on the west coast of Florida. We believe that one girl can make a difference, and that girls together can change the world.
IRS990.MissionDescription: Girl Scouting builds girls of courage, confidence, and character who make the world a better place. Girl Scouts of Gulfcoast Florida, Inc, serves 10 counties on the west coast of Florida. During FY 2010 3,190 adult volunteers worked in partnership with 10,578 girls in grades K-12 as coaches and mentors through participation in a variety of pathways (troop, series, event, travel, virtual and camp). Leadership experiences for girls are what make Girl Scouting unique. Activities (girls discover who they are and their potential, girls connect with others and girls take action to improve their communities and the world) and processes (girl led, cooperative and experiential learning) are measured by 15 outcome criteria to determine their effectiveness.
IRS990.Description: Membership Services: provides support to girls and adult volunteers in Charlotte, Collier, Desoto, Glades, Hardee, Hendry, Highlands, Lee, Manatee, and Sarasota counties who participate in the Girl Scout Leadership Experience through a troop pathway. Staff recruit, select, supervise, recognize and retain volunteers who deliver the leadership experience to girls. Girl Scouting is open to all girls (K-12) and their families in the service area. Staff insure that all girls have access to Girl Scouting through a variety of marketing, educational and outreach efforts. We provide financial support for girls who might otherwise be unable to participate due to financial limitations.

Activity2.Description: Special Programs: Girl Scouts work in partnership with caring, committed adults who provide programs to girls to help them develop leadership skills and qualities that will serve them all their lives - like strong values, social conscience, and conviction about their own potential and self-worth. Program pathways including series, events, travel, and virtual experiences allow girls to explore specific interests such as healthy living, the environment, STEM (science, technology, engineering and math), business literacy and entrepreneurship and the arts. During 2009-2010 we provided special programs such as "411 on Middle School", "Healthy Girls Initiative", "Baby think it over" and the "Get Real Mentoring Program". Girl Scouts of Gulfcoast Florida, Inc.'s programs are developed based on Girl Scouts of the USA's model for the Girl Scout Leadership Experience. The Girl Scout Leadership Experience has been shown to help girls improve their performance in several categories. One example is related to school success as evidenced by better school attendance, higher scores on FCAT's in math and reading, fewer referrals for behavioral problems, and fewer in-school suspensions

Activity3.Description: Camp Pathway: Girl Scouts of Gulfcoast Florida, Inc. provides two camps and eight Girl Scout facilities for the delivery of the Girl Scout Leadership Experience. These facilities are used by girls, adult volunteers and the community for girl meetings, special programs, first overnights, neighborhood events, adult trainings and recognitions and community collaborations. Camps offer girls the opportunity to gain confidence in their own abilities and improve self esteem through activities including kayaking, archery, high and low ropes courses, and horseback riding. Girls learn about the environment and how they can improve the planet's health by participation in the study of wetlands, wildlife, and conservation techniques.

Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: Schedule I, Part I, Line 2: MOST OF THE ASSISTANCE TO GIRLS IS IN THE FORM OF MEMBERSHIP DUES PAID TO GIRL SCOUTS OF THE USA AND PROGRAMS PROVIDED BY THE COUNCIL. IN ADDITION, ASSISTANCE IS GIVEN FOR UNIFORM COMPONENTS AND GIRL SCOUT TRIPS. TO QUALIFY FOR SCHOLARSHIPS, THE GIRLS MUST COMPLETE AN APPLICATION.
